   "source": [
    "# 07 · Concentration Profiles & Cross-Assay Concordance\n",
    "\n",
    "Purpose: summarise oxidized/reduced/total scytonemin versus dose, reproduce the trimmed-mean \n",
    "statistics from thesis pp. 32–35, and compare DAD vs chromatogram concentrations via Deming \n",
    "regression (Figure 7). No raw Waters exports are required; we rely entirely on the packaged \n",
    "Stage B/C outputs produced by `make reproduce`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Inputs\n",
    "- `data/raw/initial_calibration/DAD_to_Concentration_AUC/treatments_corrected_amounts.csv` — dry-weight amounts (mg·gDW⁻¹).\n",
    "- `data/raw/initial_calibration/DAD_to_Concentration_AUC/treatments_concentration_raw.csv` — intermediate chromatogram fits.\n",
    "- `data/reference/initial_calibration/sample_id_truth.csv` — mapping from sample to treatment/dose metadata.\n",
    "- `data/reference/initial_calibration/diode_array_auc.csv` — DAD AUCs for Deming regression."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from __future__ import annotations\n",
    "\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from math import sqrt\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n",
    "STAGE_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'raw' / 'initial_calibration' / 'DAD_to_Concentration_AUC'\n",
    "REF_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'reference' / 'initial_calibration'\n",
    "\n",
    "treatments_corrected_path = STAGE_DIR / 'treatments_corrected_amounts.csv'\n",
    "treatments_raw_path = STAGE_DIR / 'treatments_concentration_raw.csv'\n",
    "sample_truth_path = REF_DIR / 'sample_id_truth.csv'\n",
    "dad_auc_path = REF_DIR / 'diode_array_auc.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', context='talk')\n",
    "treatments_corrected_path, treatments_raw_path"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "amounts = pd.read_csv(treatments_corrected_path)\n",
    "stage_raw = pd.read_csv(treatments_raw_path)\n",
    "sample_truth = pd.read_csv(sample_truth_path)\n",
    "dad_auc = pd.read_csv(dad_auc_path)\n",
    "amounts.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Helper Functions\n",
    "- 20% trimmed mean (drop highest/lowest replicate).\n",
    "- 95% confidence interval using t distribution (df = n_eff − 1).\n",
    "- Deming regression with λ = 1 (equal variance assumption)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from scipy import stats  # optional; if unavailable, replace with custom t critical values\n",
    "\n",
    "def trimmed_mean_ci(values: np.ndarray, trim: float = 0.2, alpha: float = 0.05) -> tuple[float, float, float]:\n",
    "    values = np.asarray(values, dtype=float)\n",
    "    n = values.size\n",
    "    k = int(np.floor(trim * n))\n",
    "    if n - 2 * k <= 0:\n",
    "        raise ValueError('Not enough points after trimming')\n",
    "    trimmed = np.sort(values)[k:n - k]\n",
    "    mean = trimmed.mean()\n",
    "    sd = trimmed.std(ddof=1) if trimmed.size > 1 else 0.0\n",
    "    se = sd / sqrt(trimmed.size) if trimmed.size > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "    tcrit = stats.t.ppf(1 - alpha / 2, df=trimmed.size - 1) if trimmed.size > 1 else 0.0\n",
    "    margin = tcrit * se\n",
    "    return mean, mean - margin, mean + margin\n",
    "\n",
    "def deming_regression(x: np.ndarray, y: np.ndarray, lambda_ratio: float = 1.0) -> tuple[float, float]:\n",
    "    x = np.asarray(x, dtype=float)\n",
    "    y = np.asarray(y, dtype=float)\n",
    "    x_mean = x.mean()\n",
    "    y_mean = y.mean()\n",
    "    s_xx = np.mean((x - x_mean) ** 2)\n",
    "    s_yy = np.mean((y - y_mean) ** 2)\n",
    "    s_xy = np.mean((x - x_mean) * (y - y_mean))\n",
    "    term = s_yy - lambda_ratio * s_xx\n",
    "    slope = (term + np.sqrt(term ** 2 + 4 * lambda_ratio * s_xy ** 2)) / (2 * s_xy)\n",
    "    intercept = y_mean - slope * x_mean\n",
    "    return intercept, slope\n",
    "\n",
    "trimmed_mean_ci(np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Join Dose Metadata\n",
    "Map sample IDs to treatment labels and UV dose percentages."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "amounts = amounts.merge(sample_truth[['sample_id', 'treatment', 'sample_origin']], on='sample_id', how='left')\n",
    "amounts.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Trimmed Means & Confidence Intervals\n",
    "Compute 20% trimmed means per treatment/form and plot dose-response curves (Figure 6 analogue)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = []\n",
    "for (treatment, form), group in amounts.groupby(['treatment', 'form']):\n",
    "    mean, lo, hi = trimmed_mean_ci(group['amount_mg_per_gDW'].to_numpy(), trim=0.2)\n",
    "    results.append({'treatment': treatment, 'form': form, 'trimmed_mean': mean, 'ci_lo': lo, 'ci_hi': hi})\n",
    "trimmed_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n",
    "trimmed_df\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "order = sorted(trimmed_df['treatment'].unique(), key=lambda x: int(x.split('_')[-1]))\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9, 6))\n",
    "for form, data in trimmed_df.groupby('form'):\n",
    "    data = data.set_index('treatment').loc[order].reset_index()\n",
    "    plt.plot(data['treatment'], data['trimmed_mean'], marker='o', label=form)\n",
    "    plt.fill_between(data['treatment'], data['ci_lo'], data['ci_hi'], alpha=0.2)\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Amount (mg·gDW⁻¹)')\n",
    "plt.title('Trimmed mean ±95% CI (20% trim)')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Quadratic Overlays\n",
    "Fit a quadratic to the total scytonemin series to illustrate the rise-then-soften behaviour (Figure 8)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "total_curve = trimmed_df[trimmed_df['form'] == 'total'].set_index('treatment').loc[order].reset_index()\n",
    "x = np.arange(len(total_curve))\n",
    "coeffs = np.polyfit(x, total_curve['trimmed_mean'], deg=2)\n",
    "quad = np.polyval(coeffs, x)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "plt.plot(order, total_curve['trimmed_mean'], marker='o', label='Trimmed mean')\n",
    "plt.plot(order, quad, linestyle='--', color='black', label='Quadratic fit')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Total amount (mg·gDW⁻¹)')\n",
    "plt.title('Quadratic overlay — total scytonemin')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Deming Regression (Chrom vs DAD)\n",
    "Reproduce slopes/intercepts comparable to Figure 7."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "merged = stage_raw.pivot_table(index='sample_id', columns='form', values='conc_mg_ml').reset_index()\n",
    "dad_pivot = dad_auc[dad_auc['sample_category'] == 'sample'].pivot_table(index='sample_id', columns='spectrum_state', values='auc_corrected')\n",
    "comparison = merged.merge(dad_pivot, left_on='sample_id', right_index=True, how='inner')\n",
    "comparison.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "deming_results = []\n",
    "mapping = {\n",
    "    'total': 'sample_total',\n",
    "    'oxidized': 'sample_oxidized',\n",
    "    'reduced': 'sample_reduced',\n",
    "}\n",
    "for form, col in mapping.items():\n",
    "    intercept, slope = deming_regression(comparison[col], comparison[form])\n",
    "    r = np.corrcoef(comparison[col], comparison[form])[0, 1]\n",
    "    deming_results.append({'form': form, 'intercept': intercept, 'slope': slope, 'r': r})\n",
    "deming_df = pd.DataFrame(deming_results)\n",
    "deming_df
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Compare the slopes to the thesis targets: Total ≈ 1.88, Ox ≈ 2.03, Red ≈ 1.09."
   ]
  }
